laboratory_examinations.findings: Trace right pleural effusion with mild to moderate bilateral dependent atelectasis; the liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation with no focal lesions; mild intrahepatic biliary dilatation; gallbladder distended with thickened wall and extensive pericholecystic fat stranding; hyperdense gallstone in the gallbladder fundus measuring 5 mm; pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands normal; subcentimeter right renal hypodensities likely cysts; diverticulosis of the colon; small amount of nonhemorrhagic free pelvic fluid; no abdominal aortic aneurysm but extensive atherosclerotic disease noted.
Escherichia coli detected; values indicate a lower limit of 2.7 mg/dL.
